    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSIGINT (ctrl+c) is no longer forwarded to the terminal.\n\nThis works fine in v0.11.6 but not in v0.12.1.\n\nI'm on Windows11, Powershell v7.5.4\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI have a program that is something like this:\n```c++\n#include <csignal>\n\nint main()\n{\n        ctrl_c_handler = []{\n            std::cout << \"Ctrl-c pressed, stopping runner\" << std::endl;\n        };\n        std::signal(SIGINT, signal_handler);\n\n        // Some more stuff\n\n}\n\n```\n\nnvim  --clean\n:term\n// start the program\npress <C-c>\nNothing happens\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIn v0.11.6 I would get \"Ctrl-c pressed, stopping runner\" to the terminal\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezTerm/cmd/Windows Terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop",
